# Claude Code Configuration for Gas Town

## Context Priority
1. `.ai/context/overview.md` - Always read first
2. `.ai/maps/component-map.json` - For navigation
3. `.ai/guides/common-tasks.md` - For operations

## File Navigation
Use component map at `.ai/maps/component-map.json` to find implementations quickly.

## Coding Standards
- Follow existing patterns in codebase
- CLI commands use Cobra framework
- Managers handle business logic
- Types defined in `types.go` files
- Error handling with `fmt.Errorf` and `%w` verb
- Tests use table-driven patterns where appropriate

## Testing
- Add tests for every new feature
- Use `*_test.go` files alongside source
- Integration tests use `*_integration_test.go` naming
- Test helpers in `internal/cmd/test_helpers_test.go`

## Architecture Awareness
- Two-level beads: town-level (hq-*) vs rig-level (project prefix)
- Agent roles have distinct lifecycles (persistent vs ephemeral)
- Work attribution via identity system
- GUPP principle: work on hook must be executed

## Common Patterns
- Commands: `internal/cmd/<command>.go` with Cobra
- Managers: `internal/<component>/manager.go`
- Types: `internal/<component>/types.go`
- Templates: `internal/templates/roles/<role>.md.tmpl`

## When Adding Features
1. Determine scope (town-level vs rig-level)
2. Choose appropriate storage (beads vs ephemeral)
3. Integrate with existing systems (mail, hooks, convoys)
4. Follow patterns in `.ai/guides/adding-features.md`
5. Update component map and documentation
